# Banking Coding Standards

Follow these standards for all code changes:

- Never use `any`; use `unknown` with narrowing or type guards.
- Never read `process.env` directly in app code; use `app-config.ts` (preferred) or `lib/env.ts`.
- Implement all data mutations through Server Actions, not API routes.
- Avoid N+1 queries; use eager loading for related data.
- Keep TypeScript strict-safe and prefer explicit return types for exported functions.

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD
const token: any = process.env.API_TOKEN;

// GOOD (preferred)
import { plaid } from "@/app-config";
const clientId = plaid.PLAID_CLIENT_ID;

// GOOD (backward compat)
import { env } from "@/lib/env";
const token: string = env.ENCRYPTION_KEY;
```

```typescript
// BAD
export async function updateUser(req: Request) {
  // mutation logic in API route
}

// GOOD
"use server";

export async function updateUser(input: unknown) {
  // validate input, run mutation, return { ok, error? }
}
```
